Filter missing values by proportion

Source: R/Filtering.R
MVrowsTagToOne_HB.Rd

Remove lines in the data according to the proportion of missing values. This proportion is calculated differently depending on whether we want a certain proportion of missing values (NA) to remain on: * the entire matrix, regardless of the conditions: the rows containing a proportion of NA equal or below the threshold will be kept. * all the conditions: the lines for which all the conditions have a NA proportion equal to or less than the fixed proportion will be kept. * at least one condition: the lines for which at least one condition is equal to or less than the fixed proportion of NA will be kept.

MVrowsTagToOne_HB(obj, sTab, int.prop, mode = "None")

Arguments

obj

An object of class SummarizedExperiment containing quantitative data and phenotype data.
sTab

xxxx
int.prop

float between 0 and 1 corresponding to the proportion of intensities to keep in the lines.
mode

character string. Four possibilities corresponding to the description above: "None", WholeMatrix", "AllCond" and "AtLeastOneCond".

Value

the object given as input but with the lines not respecting the proportion of NA requested in less.

Details

Author

H?l?ne Borges, Samuel Wieczorek

Examples

library(QFeatures)
utils::data(Exp1_R25_prot, package='DAPARdata2')
obj <- Exp1_R25_pept
sTab <- colData(obj)

obj <- MVrowsTagToOne_HB(obj, sTab, mode = 'AtLeastOneCond', int.prop = 0.7)

#> Choosen proportion of intensities to be present: 0.7
#> Choosen mode: AtLeastOneCond
#> for condition 10fmol number of samples is 3, so missing value threshold is 3 
#> for condition 25fmol number of samples is 3, so missing value threshold is 3 
#> 
na_filter_percent <- VariableFilter(field = "tagNA", value = "0", condition = "==")
obj <- filterFeaturesSam(object = obj, i = 2, name = 'na_filter_percent', filter=na_filter_percent)
obj <- removeAdditionalCol(obj, "tagNA")
